deck: Assassin for N.E.M.O
description:
Broadside is the go to guy for N.E.M.O when it comes to disposing of troublesome Atlanteans. An underboss in charge of their wetwork operations, he is an assassin tasked with eliminating Joanna Stubbs due to her uncles connections to their organization, he'd been tailing her for some time until Black Manta established himself as his new leader.

While tailing miss Stubbs at a seafood restaurant she had a chance encounter with Aquaman's wife Mera. The minute Broadside saw the both of them together he went on the offensive, dropping his cloak and coming at them guns ablaze with wristmounted munitions capable of hurting even the likes of Arthur's betrothed. Having been distracted by his initial quarry however, the would be assailant met his match in the mermaid as she bound him with water.

Broadside opted to release a timed charge to aid in his escape in order to avoid capture. Knowing full well she'd leap to the rescue. As Mera suppressed the explosion with her powers dividing her attentions, loosening her grip on him in the confusion. Eventually broadside made his escape after she dealt with the explosion.

Weapons & Equipment

Wrist Mounted Munitions

Twin Arm Cannons

Broadside uses a pair of ballistic launch devices to propel explosive possibly active uranium shell casings which can pierce and rend even the dense skin of an Atlantean or Xebelian hide. Their use of ignition is a mystery, possibly through electromagnetic induction of some sort.

Mini-Mines

His armaments also dispense small but powerful explosive charges with enough destructive force to collapse building structures.
name: Broadside

deck: George R. Blake is Daphne Blake's father.
description:
George R. Blake is Daphne Blake's father.

In the series A Pup Named Scooby Doo, we learn his name and that he made his fortune as the creator of the product "Blake's Bubbles", though the series Mystery Incorporated gives the Blake family a more "old money" feel. More credence is given to the "old money" theory by the number of castles in the family, in various episodes and movies.

A few years before A Pup Named Scooby Doo, the author Horace J. Elias wrote a series of Scooby-Doo books where he uses George R. Blake (referred to only as Daphne's Father) as a plot device to get the Mystery Incorporated from their hometown, to the various places the mysteries took place, California, Africa, etc. George would gather the team and then explain why they need to go solve the mystery.
name: George R. Blake

deck: Paper-themed robber operating in Central City
description:
Origin

Nothing is known about Papercut's origins. He was presumably born with his metahuman abilities. He at some point turned to a life of crime, emboldened by the absence of the Rogues from Central City.

Creation

Papercut was created by Joshua Williamson and Felipe Watanabe. He made his first appearance in The Flash #10.

Major Story Arcs

The Flash

Operating as a mugger in a park, Papercut is confronted first by Kid Flash, whom he nearly defeats, and then by the Flash, by whom he is defeated. He is taken by the Flash to Iron Heights, and imprisoned there. He becomes increasingly vocal about the time of the Rogues having passed, and attempts to install himself as the new criminal mastermind in Central City. He is confronted and beaten by Captain Cold when the latter is returned to prison.

Powers and Abilities

Papercut has the ability to control wood and wood-based products. He finds it painful to control wood on a grand scale, and typically uses his powers to create razor-sharp paper weapons. He is pretty good at origami.

Weapons and Equipment

Papercut often carries paper which he folds into stars and sharpens with his powers into weaponry.
